  "plan": "## HeatMapImage GenePattern Module — Implementation Plan\n\n### 1. Overview\nHeatMapImage is a GenePattern module that Creates a heat map from a dataset\n\n### 2. Parameters\nThe module exposes 14 parameters:\n- Required: input.dataset, output, output.format, column.size, row.size\n- Optional: show.grid, grid.color, show.row.descriptions, show.row.names, rows.to.highlight, row.highlight.color, color.scheme, color.palette, use.color.gradient\n\n### 3. Command Line\n```\n<java> -Djava.awt.headless\\=true <java_flags> -jar <libdir>heatmapimage-o.jar <input.dataset> <output> <output.format> -c<row.size> -r<column.size> -g<show.grid> -l<grid.color> -a<show.row.descriptions> -s<show.row.names> -f<rows.to.highlight> -h<row.highlight.color> -n<color.scheme> -m<color.palette> -u<use.color.gradient>\n```\n\n### 4. Docker Image\nDocker image: \n\n### 5. Validation Strategy\n- Validate all required parameters are provided\n- Validate file formats match expected extensions\n- Check parameter value ranges where applicable\n\n### 6. Implementation Roadmap\nPhase 1: Wrapper script implementation\nPhase 2: Docker container setup\nPhase 3: Parameter validation and error handling\nPhase 4: Testing and documentation",
